## PDF EXPORT (when required)

Use `html2pdf.js` via CDN:
```html
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/html2pdf.js/0.10.1/html2pdf.bundle.min.js"></script>
```

**Always use the cloned DOM approach** to avoid mutating the live page:
```js
function exportPDF(elementId, filename) {
  const source = document.getElementById(elementId);
  const clone = source.cloneNode(true);
  clone.style.background = '#0B1C3D';
  clone.style.padding = '24px';

  const opt = {
    margin:      [10, 10, 10, 10],
    filename:    filename,
    image:       { type: 'jpeg', quality: 0.98 },
    html2canvas: { scale: 2, useCORS: true, backgroundColor: '#0B1C3D' },
    jsPDF:       { unit: 'mm', format: 'a4', orientation: 'portrait' }
  };

  html2pdf().set(opt).from(clone).save();
}
```

The export button should be styled gold and placed in the tool header or footer. It should NOT appear in the PDF itself (add `class="no-print"` and `@media print { .no-print { display: none; } }`).

